title: First Christian Church Soccer Field
description: A nice communal place to play soccer
statement: This is a public-use soccer field at a church

title: Twisted Root Gas Pump
description: A repurposed gas pump at Twisted Root Burger Company
statement: Twisted Root is a really cool and locally owned burger joint, south of Birmingham. This piece of art would be a great portal.

title: Lakeshore Trail Footbridge
description: Concrete footbridge allowing foot travel over Shade's Creek
statement: This is a notable structure in a public park

title: Community
description: A mural featuring dozens of names coming together to form the Homewood community.
statement: This is a mural that helps beautify the Homewood area.

title: Red Mountain Park Pollinator Garden Pergola
description: This pergola at Red Mountain Park is located in the far southwest reaches of the park. It rewards the few who travel this far out with a nice place to swing in the shade of evergreens.
statement: This is a hidden gem of a resting feature in a public park

title: Alabama Great Seal
description: This bronze seal of Alabama sits at almost 3 feet in diameter, embedded in the floor of the Shelby Biomedical Sciences Building at the University of Alabama Birmingham.
statement: This seal has cultural value, as it is the state seal of Alabama. The Shelby building is the only building at UAB to sport this seal too.

title: Birmingham: Tree City
description: This sign marks the entrance to Birmingham Proper, with its nickname as Tree City.
statement: This sign marks the boundary to Birmingham City Limits. it is located in George Ward Park with easy pedestrian access

title: Goldenrod Pavillion
description: Goldenrod Pavillion at Oak Mountain park
statement: This is a pavillion in a public park

title: Lake Payne Pond Pavilion
description: One of the three pavilions at the Lake Payne Recreation Area. This pavilion is located just up a hill from a small pond, and gets an elevated view of Lake Payne.
statement: This is a pavilion in a public park. The pavilion has safe pedestrian access.

title: Lake Payne North Pavilion
description: One of three pavilions located at Lake Payne. This pavilion is located at the northern shore, right by the water, making for amazing views!
statement: This is a pavilion in a public park with safe pedestrian access.

title: Lake Payne Swimming Beach - West
description: This sign helps mark one of the two designated swimming areas at Lake Payne. This area is located on the west side of the lake, near the campsite with running water and electricity. It is highly recommended to swim at this designated area, as it is cleared of vegetation and away from fishing areas.
statement: This is a swimming area in a lake in a public park. There is a man-made enclosure of pipe and rope that demarcates the boundary of the swim area (can barely be seen in the background of the supporting photo). This waypoint qualifies under the category of outdoor recreation. I was unable to get a good picture of the swimming area because it was in use by other campers, but it can be seen from a top-down view with the satellite view.

title: Lake Payne Primitive Campsite #23
description: One of the primitive campsites on the east side of Lake Payne. A great place to come out and connect with the outdoors.
statement: This is a public campsite in a public park

title: Lake Payne East Campground Directory Sign
description: Directory sign on the east side of Lake Payne. This sign is located on the primitive camping side of the lake, pointing to the directions of campsites and the east swimming area.
statement: This is a directory sign in a public park with safe pedestrian access. It is the only directory sign on this side of the lake, making it a very useful landmark, especially if you don't have a map of the park.

title: Lake Payne Campsite #14
description: This campsite is one of the campsites on the west side of Lake Payne, with access to running water. This particular campsite had a beautiful lookout over the lake from where it's picnic table is located.
statement: This is a campsite located in a public park

title: Welcome To Mill Hall
description: This sign on the front of the Pilot rest stop welcomes travelers to the Mill Hall borough of Pennsylvania. Located near the geographic center of the state, Mill Hall is located along Fishing Creek and Bald Eagle Creek. It is known for notable locations, like the Millbrook Playhouse and the historic Heisey House. Welcome!
statement: This is a small, but unique and newly-installed welcome sign at a rest stop in a small town. The sign being unique and promoting exploration allows this submission to qualify as a waypoint. It is located at a rest stop, which promotes further exploration and socialization.

title: Mass Central Rail Trail - 60.6 Mile Marker
description: This marker along the Mass Central Rail Trail notes the point that was historically 60.6 miles away from North Station (by rail) in Boston, when this trail was a railroad. This marker preserves the common practice of using markers to note landmarks along the railroad, in this case the nearby crossing over the Quinapoxet River near what was the Charolette Mill. Today, this humble marker continues to help guide distance along the trail in the greater MCRT system.
statement: This is a permanently installed trail marker along a hiking and biking trail that follows what was once a railroad line. This specific marker has increased significance, as it also marks distance along the original rail line, as opposed to some other markers that only mark relative distance from nearby trailheads. This marker anchors the trail in this point, helping explorers guide their way along with trail with a notable landmark. This marker is safely accessible to hikers, and per the supporting photo, there is clearly no train track anymore, and this is now a trail. More about the trail itself can be found here: https://masstrailtracker.com/map?segment=62

title: Charlotte Mill Picnic Area
description: A picnic area, equipped with picnic tables, located by the Charlotte Mill Historic Site along the Mass Central Rail Trail. It is a place to sit and relax along the trail, and enjoy a view if the Quinapoxet River.
statement: This is a permanently installed picnic area with picnic tables, which is located along a public trail. The trail encourages exploration and exercise, and the tables encourage socialization.

title: Eric and Lois Johansen Memorial Bench
description: This bench along the Holden stretch of the Mass Central Rail Trail is dedicated in the memory of Eric and Lois Johansen. They were revered members of the Holden community. They were active in many ways, including volunteering for Holden Scout Troop 182. Eric served as a local volunteer firefighter and president of the White Oaks Land Preservation, supporting greenspaces like the trail. They were granted many accolades from the community, like the "Good Neighbor Award" from the Holden Town Committee.
statement:
This is a memorial bench that is dedicated to two notable members of the Holden community. It is located along a public trail, with benches that are dedicated to individuals and families who were important and beloved in Holden throughout its history. This bench is dedicated to Eric and Lois, who spend much of their time volunteering in the town in many ways, from firefighting, to supporting local greenspaces, to supporting children sports and extracurricular activities. Both of them were very involved in the community and recognized for their efforts. Eric's obituary further describes the many contributions and awards for both Eric and Lois with their community: https://www.milesfuneralhome.com/obituaries/eric-johansen-2

This bench helps anchor a point of interest along a trail, with the bench encouraging exploration and the trail itself is on encouraging exercise and exploration.

title: Natick Mall West Directory
description: This directory sign, located on the west side of the Natick Mall, is equipped with a well-labeled map that helps mallgoers navigate the mall.
statement: This is a permanently installed place name sign, directory, and map that is located in a public mall. The map encourages exploration and the mall encourages socialization.

title: Hyper Zone Indoor Playground
description: Welcome to the Hyper Zone! The Hyper Zone is an indoor playground in the Auburn Mall, equipped with a ball pit, slides, and a series of tunnels to climb around in. Plenty of fun in any weather!
statement: The Hyper Zone is an indoor playground in a shopping mall that opened in 2025. It encourages socialization, exercise, and exploration for families with children. The mall setting further encourages socialization. More about the playground can be found on their website here: https://hyperzonema.com/

title: Historic Coretta Scott King Home
description: Obadiah ("Obie") and Bernice Scott raised their daughter, Corretta Scott King, in this house. The family attended church next door at the Mt. Tabor AME church. On June 18, 1953, Corretta would marry Dr. Martin Luther King Jr. on the lawn of this property, creating a union that would help drive the Civil Rights movement. Located directly next to the home is the family-owned general store, Scott's Grocery, which was run by Obie. The site is now a landmark on Alabama Civil Rights tours.
statement:
This is a historic home on the historic register with safe pedestrian access, including from the nearby also significant Mount Tabor AME church right next door. This is no longer a private residence, and has not been for decades. The house is maintained and preserved by the King family. It is an important preserved of civil rights history that is often frequented on Civil Rights tours to observe this site. The general store can be seen in the supporting photo. This waypoint encourages exploration for those wishing to find an important landmark and site of Civil Rights history.

More on the home and its modern state can be found here, including notes on the status of the home and no longer being a private residence:

https://www.thenationalherald.com/historic-coretta-scott-home-where-she-wed-mlk-now-forgotten/

"Cars and tour buses occasionally stop by, longtime neighbor William Carter said, but there’s no sign or historic marker to tell the property’s story. He still misses Coretta King’s parents, Obie and Bernice M. Scott, who died in 1998 and 1996, respectively."

title: Southern Specialty Welding - Metal Deer Art
description: This piece of plasma-cut painted metal depicts a scene of deer among woods and mountains. It was made in-house at Southern Specialty Welding, showcasing their high precision metal cutting to make beautiful designs. The art is located beneath the business's sign.
statement: This is a one of a kind metal sculpture that is made by the locally owned Southern Specialty Welding company. This piece is new and permanently installed. The piece is safely accessible to pedestrians via the driveway/paths around the building and nearby Heiberger Grocery convenience store. Pedestrian access can be seen in the supporting photo and on google maps. The piece encourages exploration for people to find this hidden gem of a piece of art, especially in this underdeveloped rural area.

title: Heiberger Grocery Picnic Area
description: A small shaded picnic area and table, located at the Heiberger Grocery. It's a nice place to pull off the road and have a picnic, either brought with you, or from the warm meals and snacks offered at the store.
statement: This is a permanently installed rest area, picnic area, and picnic table at a rural locally owned convenience store, which is open to the public. This picnic area and convenience store promotes socialization and exploration. Per Niantic waypoint criteria, this waypoint should qualify as it matches a waypoint subject of being a public-access picnic area/table and promotes socialization and exploration in a rural area. The subject is not the grocery store itself (which would be a generic business), the subject is the picnic area/table, which qualifies. Niantic's ruling on picnic areas, for further validation: https://community.wayfarer.nianticlabs.com/t/picnic-areas/12468

title: New Antioch Baptist Church
description: The New Antioch Baptist Church serves the Baptist congregation of Bibb County and the surrounding area. As its name suggests, the congregation traces its lineage from a congregation in nearby Antioch, which was founded in 1833, and is one of the oldest Baptist congregations in Alabama.
statement: This is a church with cultural significance to the area, stemming from a nearly 200 year old congregation. The church encourages socialization and exploration.

title: Broaster Rooster Statue
description: A 6 foot tall statue of a rooster, outside the Friendly Mart for Broaster Chickens. This is one big clucker!
statement: This is a unique and permanently installed sculpture of a giant chicken that is a small roadside attraction at a restaurant and convenience store. The chicken makes for an interesting photo opportunity, promoting exploration.

title: Discover Delaware Map
description: A map of Delaware and surrounding states, with attractions highlighted to give travelers inspiration of where to take their journey next. This map is located in the Biden Welcome Center, the largest road travel hub in Delaware and a gateway to exploration innthe state.
statement: This is a permanently installed detailed travel map in a welcome center. It promotes exploration by helping travelers identify points of interest in the state or surrounding states to explore. As such, this map is a huge proponent of exploration, encouraging further travel. It is located in a frequently visited welcome center that encourages socialization. It is also unique, being the only large and detailed map in the travel center.

title: Biden Welcome Center Picnic Area
description: An outdoor picnic area consisting of multiple tables, located at the Biden Welcome Center in Newark, Delaware. It's a great place to pull off and have a picnic, or have a meal from one of the many restaurants inside the welcome center.
statement: This is a permanently installed picnic area at a welcome center. The subject of this waypoint is the picnic area, and is separate from the existing waypoint for the welcome center, as the picnic area is worthy of having its own independent waypoint. This is a public access and permanently installed picnic area and picnic tables that encourages exploration and socialization. Per Niantic ruling in May 2024, they note that picnic areas like these are valid as long as they fulfill other validation criteria. More on the Niantic ruling: https://community.wayfarer.nianticlabs.com/t/picnic-areas/12468

title: Joe Tea Mural
description: A mural depicting a classic vintage Americana-style advertisement for Joe Tea, a small regional tea brand around the DE/NJ/NY area. The mural is located in the Joe Biden Travel Plaza in Newark, Delaware. The plaza is a place where two important Joes meet, for tea and for presidency. The mural greets travelers with a kind message, "Enjoy Your Journey."
statement: This is a permanently installed mural in the style of a vintage ad for a locally owned and small regional tea company, Joe Tea. The mural decorates the interior of a major rest area and plaza along one of the largest highways in Delaware. The mural promotes exploration to find this piece of unique art, like some other existing mural pieces at this rest area. The rest area itself promotes socialization as well.
